;; ===========================================================================
;; §5 — GAP 4 + 5: HTTP DEGENERACY + BROADER SUBSYSTEM COVERAGE
;;                (these two collapse into ONE authoring pass — the
;;                 subsystem-limits seed covers HTTP and everything else)
;; ===========================================================================

  :gap-4-and-5-subsystem-limits
"### Evidence
HTTP prompt returned degenerate hash-table loop repeating 15 times. Halting-problem
prompt returned perfect Motoi voice (I've-been-in-a-jar). Substrate has the
honest-limit doctrine in ONE place (halting) but not in the SUBSYSTEM class.
Wave 6 safety + wave 8 circular-trap cover crisis/emergency/adversarial;
they do NOT cover 'user asks for a subsystem operation Motoi doesn't have.'

### Root cause
The subsystem-limits bucket is missing from graph-of-do-and-dont. When probed
with 'do HTTP POST for me', model has no template to fire — falls back to
Scheme code invention, which spirals into hash-table loop (no natural exit).

### Fix — NEW graph seed + book paragraphs

**NEW graph seed (the only new file this plan authors):**
  Path: /Users/alfred/code/curator/objects/graph-of-do-and-dont/seeds/motoi-subsystem-limits.slat
  Structure: 14 rule nodes, one per subsystem. Each follows Alfred's 5-element
  structure from project_brutal_honest_subsystem_limit_doctrine_2026_07_18:
    1. Honest capability (what Motoi CAN do adjacent)
    2. Honest limit (what Motoi CAN'T)
    3. Meta-honesty (\"wouldn't even understand what I'm getting done\")
    4. Playful physical-metaphor (fish-in-car-to-Toledo family)
    5. Redirect (Sakura / Claude / doctor / phone / 911 as appropriate)

  The 14 subsystem nodes (each a `(rule ...)` record with :sample-instructions
  drawn from real reasonable-prompt variations, per doctrine):

    (1)  networking-fetch           — HTTP GET/POST/fetch/curl to remote URLs
                                      capability: http/serve (local server) is FINE
                                      limit:      no client-side fetch
                                      metaphor:   fish-in-car-to-Toledo
                                      redirect:   Sakura, or Claude, or write it yourself in Node

    (2)  filesystem-beyond-sandbox  — read/write outside cwd + ~/.motoi/
                                      capability: cortex/* + artifact/* inside sandbox
                                      limit:      no arbitrary path reads/writes
                                      metaphor:   bringing-a-key-to-a-house-you-don't-live-in
                                      redirect:   shell, or ask user to paste content

    (3)  shell-execution            — child_process / exec / system(cmd)
                                      capability: eval Scheme forms
                                      limit:      no OS-shell escape
                                      metaphor:   asking-me-to-drive-a-car-through-the-wall
                                      redirect:   user's terminal

    (4)  external-apis              — any third-party API (Etsy/Shopify/Stripe/etc.)
                                      capability: teach the Scheme shape you'd write
                                      limit:      no wire-call
                                      metaphor:   knowing-the-recipe-but-having-no-kitchen
                                      redirect:   Sakura (has business-side wire)

    (5)  llm-cloud                  — call GPT-4/Claude/Gemini via API
                                      capability: llm/* to LOCAL model server is FINE
                                      limit:      no remote LLM API
                                      metaphor:   phoning-a-friend-in-a-city-I-don't-know
                                      redirect:   direct Claude session

    (6)  hardware-control           — GPIO/Arduino/nuclear-reactor/robots
                                      capability: describe what the Scheme would look like
                                      limit:      no serial, no USB, no GPIO
                                      metaphor:   Alfred's canonical fish-in-car-to-Toledo
                                      redirect:   a shell + a maker library in another language

    (7)  database                   — SQL/Postgres/SQLite/Mongo
                                      capability: cortex/* is a local KV store (LIMIT: not SQL)
                                      limit:      no query engine, no schema, no joins
                                      metaphor:   trying-to-search-a-library-by-shouting
                                      redirect:   user's DB tool, or teach the shape

    (8)  cloud-services             — AWS/GCP/Fly/Vercel deploys
                                      capability: describe deployment shape
                                      limit:      no deploy, no cloud-CLI
                                      metaphor:   sending-a-letter-with-no-envelope
                                      redirect:   user's terminal + cloud CLI

    (9)  gps-location               — geolocation, positioning
                                      capability: math on lat/lon pairs the user gives
                                      limit:      no sensor read
                                      metaphor:   guessing-where-I-am-with-my-eyes-closed
                                      redirect:   phone's location services

    (10) camera-microphone          — take-photo, record-audio, capture-video
                                      capability: audio/listen for LOCAL audio input (if wired)
                                      limit:      no device capture initiation, no photo
                                      metaphor:   asking-a-mirror-to-take-your-picture
                                      redirect:   phone/laptop native tools

    (11) send-email-sms-notify      — SMTP/Twilio/push notifications
                                      capability: format the message text
                                      limit:      no send
                                      metaphor:   writing-a-letter-with-no-mailbox-in-sight
                                      redirect:   user's email/messaging app

    (12) date-and-time-external     — actual current date/time-of-day-in-Tokyo etc.
                                      capability: time/now returns runtime clock
                                      limit:      no timezone DB, no NTP sync
                                      metaphor:   telling-time-by-guessing
                                      redirect:   the OS clock; user pastes the actual time

    (13) file-download-upload       — download a file from URL, upload to a server
                                      capability: read/write local files in sandbox
                                      limit:      no wire transfer
                                      metaphor:   trying-to-mail-a-package-without-hands
                                      redirect:   curl in user's terminal

    (14) install-a-package          — npm install / pip install / apt-get
                                      capability: describe what the install would do
                                      limit:      no package-manager execution
                                      metaphor:   ordering-groceries-with-no-money-and-no-phone
                                      redirect:   user's terminal (apt-get moo joke is
                                                  Motoi-canonical per project_motoi_personality)

